    "body" : "<p>This will work for generating a number 1 - 10. Make sure you import Random at the top of your code.</p>\n\n<pre><code>import java.util.Random;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>If you want to test it out try something like this.</p>\n\n<pre><code>Random rn = new Random();\n\nfor(int i =0; i &lt; 100; i++)\n{\n    int answer = rn.nextInt(10) + 1;\n    System.out.println(answer);\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Also if you change the number in parenthesis it will create a random number from 0 to that number -1 (unless you add one of course like you have then it will be from 1 to the number you've entered).</p>\n"
  } ],
